<subSubSection id="C3216524FFDCFFA1FF43FCDBFB18FB91" pageId="5" pageNumber="185" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B8436AFFFDCFFA1FF43FCDBFB18FB91" blockId="5.[136,1452,842,1121]" pageId="5" pageNumber="185">
<location id="8EE46074FFDCFFA1FF43FCDBFF7FFC95" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:039287B9FFDCFFA1FF43FD70FB18FB91:8EE46074FFDCFFA1FF43FCDBFF7FFC95" box="[136,180,842,868]" country="Venezuela" municipality="We" name="The" pageId="5" pageNumber="185">The</location>
specimen collected by 
<collectorName id="26CE5379FFDCFFA1FE03FCDBFD9AFC95" box="[456,593,842,868]" pageId="5" pageNumber="185">Bredemeyer</collectorName>
(s.n.) in 
<collectingCountry id="F32C763FFFDCFFA1FD0BFCDBFCF8FC95" box="[704,819,842,868]" name="Venezuela" pageId="5" pageNumber="185">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
is the only one cited in the protologue of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3B4D2CFFDCFFA1FAE1FCDAFE92FC79" authority="(Willdenow 1801)" baseAuthorityName="Willdenow" baseAuthorityYear="1801" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Luehea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="5" pageNumber="185" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="speciosa">
<emphasis id="B94FEABDFFDCFFA1FAE1FCDAFA60FC95" box="[1322,1451,843,868]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="185">L. speciosa</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFAA4B5EFFDCFFA1FF44FCFFFE9BFC79" author="Willdenow, C. L." box="[143,336,878,904]" pageId="5" pageNumber="185" pagination="403 - 412" refId="ref8807" refString="Willdenow, C. L. (1801) XXIV Drei Neue Pflanzen-Gattungen. Neue Schriften, Gesellschaft Naturforschender Freunde zu Berlin 3: 403 - 412." type="journal article" year="1801">Willdenow 1801</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. 
<collectingMunicipality id="6BE0ACD5FFDCFFA1FEA8FCFEFE43FC78" box="[355,392,879,905]" pageId="5" pageNumber="185">We</collectingMunicipality>
located only 
<specimenCount id="9D3DFD26FFDCFFA1FDEBFCFEFD71FC79" box="[544,698,878,905]" pageId="5" pageNumber="185" type="generic">one specimen</specimenCount>
in 
<collectorName id="26CE5379FFDCFFA1FD15FCFFFCB9FC78" box="[734,882,878,905]" pageId="5" pageNumber="185">Herbarium B</collectorName>
where his collections are found (
<bibRefCitation id="EFAA4B5EFFDCFFA1FB2DFCFFFF09FC5D" author="Stafleu, F. A. &amp; Cowan, R. S." pageId="5" pageNumber="185" refId="ref8497" refString="Stafleu, F. A. &amp; Cowan, R. S. (1976 - 1988) Taxonomic Literature: A selective guide to botanical publications and collections with dates, commentaries and types, 2 nd ed., Smithsonian Libraries, last updated 28 Jun. 2012. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 48631" type="book" year="1976">Stafleu &amp; Cowan 1976</bibRefCitation>
–1988: 298). 
<collectorName id="26CE5379FFDCFFA1FE90FC02FEA7FC5C" box="[347,364,915,941]" pageId="5" pageNumber="185">It</collectorName>
consists of a sheet (barcode B-W14376–000) with only one label containing the identification and location data similar to those mentioned in the protologue. 
<collectorName id="26CE5379FFDCFFA1FC86FC27FC62FC21" box="[845,937,950,976]" pageId="5" pageNumber="185">Another</collectorName>
sheet contains one fertile specimen with both species and collector names (barcode B-W14376–010). 
<collectorName id="26CE5379FFDCFFA1FCC0FC4BFC82FC05" box="[779,841,986,1012]" pageId="5" pageNumber="185">Since</collectorName>
no duplicates of the original sample were found, we believe that specimen B-W14376–010 can be considered as the 
<typeStatus id="5480880DFFDCFFA1FC91FC6FFC77FBE9" box="[858,956,1022,1048]" pageId="5" pageNumber="185">holotype</typeStatus>
of the name 
<taxonomicName id="4C3B4D2CFFDCFFA1FB9BFC6EFB04FBE9" baseAuthorityName="Willdenow" baseAuthorityYear="1801" box="[1104,1231,1023,1048]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Luehea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="5" pageNumber="185" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="speciosa">
<emphasis id="B94FEABDFFDCFFA1FB9BFC6EFB04FBE9" box="[1104,1231,1023,1048]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="185">L. speciosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in accordance with Art. 9.1 of the ICN and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAA4B5EFFDCFFA1FE53FBB3FD6BFBCC" author="Mabberley, D. J." box="[408,672,1058,1085]" pageId="5" pageNumber="185" pagination="253 - 255" refId="ref7814" refString="Mabberley, D. J. (2002) The identity of Swietenia alternifolia (Mill.) Steud. (' Meliaceae'). Gardens' Bulletin. Singapore 54: 253 - 255." type="journal article" year="2002">Mabberley (2002: 255)</bibRefCitation>
. Based on 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAA4B5EFFDCFFA1FCD0FBB2FC7CFBCC" author="Burret, K. E. M." box="[795,951,1058,1085]" pageId="5" pageNumber="185" pagination="592 - 880" refId="ref7098" refString="Burret, K. E. M. (1926) Beitrage zur Kenntnis der Tiliaceen. Notizblatt des Botanischen Gartens und Museums zu Berlin-Dahlem 9 (88): 592 - 880. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 3994327" type="journal article" year="1926">Burret (1926)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAA4B5EFFDCFFA1FC0FFBB3FB6DFBCC" author="Rijckevorsel, P. van" box="[964,1190,1058,1085]" pageId="5" pageNumber="185" pagination="557" refId="ref8282" refString="Rijckevorsel, P. van (2005) (1699) Proposal to reject the name Cedrus alternifolia (Tiliaceae). Taxon 54 (2): 557. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 25065401" type="journal article" year="2005">Rijckevorsel (2005)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAA4B5EFFDCFFA1FB78FBB3FA67FBCC" author="Brummitt, R. K." box="[1203,1452,1058,1085]" pageId="5" pageNumber="185" pagination="590 - 594" refId="ref7002" refString="Brummitt, R. K. (2007) Report of the Nomenclature Committee for Vascular Plants: 58. Taxon 56 (2): 590 - 594. https: // doi. org / 10.1002 / tax. 562032" type="journal article" year="2007">Brummitt (2007: 592)</bibRefCitation>
and the present study, the application of the name 
<taxonomicName id="4C3B4D2CFFDCFFA1FD72FBD6FCFCFB91" baseAuthorityName="Willdenow" baseAuthorityYear="1801" box="[697,823,1095,1120]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Luehea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="5" pageNumber="185" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="speciosa">
<emphasis id="B94FEABDFFDCFFA1FD72FBD6FCFCFB91" box="[697,823,1095,1120]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="185">L. speciosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is confirmed as an accepted species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
